        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "An aggressive form of acute myeloid leukemia (AML) characterized by arrest of leukocyte differentiation at the promyelocyte stage due to a specific chromosomal translocation t(15;17) in myeloid cells and manifests with easy bruising hemorrhagic diathesis and fatigue."
